title: Google\Cloud\GkeMultiCloud\V1\AzureCluster
name: AzureCluster
description:
An Anthos cluster running on Azure.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.AzureCluster

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The name of this resource. Cluster names are formatted as projects/<project-number>/locations/<region>/azureClusters/<cluster-id>. See Resource Names for more details on GCP resource names.

params.name: data.description
params.description: Optional. A human readable description of this cluster. Cannot be longer than 255 UTF-8 encoded bytes.

params.name: data.azure_region
params.description: Required. The Azure region where the cluster runs. Each Google Cloud region supports a subset of nearby Azure regions. You can call [GetAzureServerConfig][google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.AzureClusters.GetAzureServerConfig] to list all supported Azure regions within a given Google Cloud region.

params.name: data.resource_group_id
params.description: Required. The ARM ID of the resource group where the cluster resources are deployed. For example: /subscriptions/<subscription-id>/resourceGroups/<resource-group-name>

params.name: data.azure_client
params.description: Required. Name of the [AzureClient][google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.AzureClient] that contains authentication configuration for how the Anthos Multi-Cloud API connects to Azure APIs. The AzureClient resource must reside on the same GCP project and region as the AzureCluster. AzureClient names are formatted as projects/<project-number>/locations/<region>/azureClients/<client-id>. See Resource Names for more details on Google Cloud resource names.

params.name: data.networking
params.description: Required. Cluster-wide networking configuration.

params.name: data.control_plane
params.description: Required. Configuration related to the cluster control plane.

params.name: data.authorization
params.description: Required. Configuration related to the cluster RBAC settings.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. The current state of the cluster.

params.name: data.endpoint
params.description: Output only. The endpoint of the cluster's API server.

params.name: data.uid
params.description: Output only. A globally unique identifier for the cluster.

params.name: data.reconciling
params.description: Output only. If set, there are currently changes in flight to the cluster.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. The time at which this cluster was created.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. The time at which this cluster was last updated.

params.name: data.etag
params.description: Allows clients to perform consistent read-modify-writes through optimistic concurrency control. Can be sent on update and delete requests to ensure the client has an up-to-date value before proceeding.

params.name: data.annotations
params.description: Optional. Annotations on the cluster. This field has the same restrictions as Kubernetes annotations. The total size of all keys and values combined is limited to 256k. Keys can have 2 segments: prefix (optional) and name (required), separated by a slash (/). Prefix must be a DNS subdomain. Name must be 63 characters or less, begin and end with alphanumerics, with dashes (-), underscores (_), dots (.), and alphanumerics between.

params.name: data.workload_identity_config
params.description: Output only. Workload Identity settings.

params.name: data.cluster_ca_certificate
params.description: Output only. PEM encoded x509 certificate of the cluster root of trust.

params.name: data.fleet
params.description: Optional. Fleet configuration.

params.name: data.managed_resources
params.description: Output only. Mananged Azure resources for this cluster.

params.name: data.logging_config
params.description: Optional. Logging configuration for this cluster.
